dcterms:description: Mujoco environments are continuous control environments used for testing reinforcement learning algorithms, providing a variety of tasks that require agents to learn complex behaviors.
dcterms:title: Mujoco environments

dcterms:description: OpenAI Gym classic control environments are a set of simple environments for testing reinforcement learning algorithms, including tasks like balancing a pole on a cart.
dcterms:title: OpenAI Gym classic control environments

dcterms:description: The Pendulum environment is a classic control task where the goal is to swing up and balance a pendulum upright.
dcterms:title: Pendulum environment

dcterms:description: The Cartpole environment is a classic control task where the objective is to balance a pole on a cart by moving the cart left or right.
dcterms:title: Cartpole environment

dcterms:description: The BipedalWalker environment is a continuous control task where the goal is to walk a bipedal robot across a terrain.
dcterms:title: BipedalWalker environment

dcterms:description: The Ant environment is a continuous control task where the objective is to make a four-legged robot walk.
dcterms:title: Ant environment

dcterms:description: The Half-Cheetah environment is a continuous control task where the goal is to make a half-cheetah robot run.
dcterms:title: Half-Cheetah environment
